.TH "csum_and_copy_from_user" 9 "csum_and_copy_from_user" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
csum_and_copy_from_user \- Copy and checksum from user space.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "__wsum" csum_and_copy_from_user
.BI "(const void __user *src "  ","
.BI "void *dst "  ","
.BI "int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src" 12
source address (user space)
.IP "dst" 12
destination address
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to be copied.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns an 32bit unfolded checksum of the buffer.
src and dst are best aligned to 64bits.
